  "learn": {
    "heading": "Divide, then keep the point",
    "intro": "<p>To divide a decimal by a whole number, divide as usual and bring the <strong>decimal point straight up</strong> into the answer. Dividing by 10 or 100 just shifts the point left.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>0.6 ÷ 2:</strong> 6 ÷ 2 = 3, bring the point up → <strong>0.3</strong>.",
      "<strong>4.8 ÷ 10:</strong> dividing by 10 shifts the point one left → <strong>0.48</strong>."
    ]
  },
